transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I wanted to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, is your name Hector?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, one moment, Hector.

Speaker 2: Alrighty, I do see that you are a VIP with us here, Hector.

Speaker 1: Do you mind if I ask why you're cancelling today?

Speaker 2: It's just too expensive.

Speaker 1: Oh, wow, okay. Well, you do not have to get it the way you're currently getting it.

Speaker 2: I mean, you don't have to get it monthly.

Speaker 1: You can get one order every five months.

Speaker 2: Get it whenever you'd like, sir.

Speaker 1: No, I just don't want any more.

Speaker 2: A month is going to be a lot for anyone.

Speaker 1: No, thank you.

Speaker 2: You do realize it wouldn't be that much, sir, if you spaced that out, right?

Speaker 1: You'd be looking at almost like $10 a month.

Speaker 2: I don't want to spend any more money on it.

Speaker 1: Okay, I mean, I do understand that, sir, but it can't be because of the price.

Speaker 2: I just don't want it anymore.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Alright, we'll cancel it out then. You won't receive this again.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
